	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Late Thursday night posts from Abashi</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=214045" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <Blockquote>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/011623.html">Abashi: quick question about surnames, just needs a yes or a no</a></B><P>

Once you make lvl 20, can you legally take the surname of an npc in the game? I know you can't take both first and last name, but say for RPing reasons you wanted your character to be related to an npc? Is that legal according to the rules?<P>

<B>Unfortunately it's not as simple as a yes or no answer, and is more the subject of a judgement call on the part of the GM and the Senior Guides. For instance, I doubt that the surname "Irontoe" would be preferable, since the Irontoe brigade is a major part of EQ lore. Other names however may be more acceptable.<P>

Contact your server GM should you have any concerns.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/011638.html">UI Improvement idea - F8 cycles through monsters</a></B><p>

I play an enchanter and one of the greatest difficulties I have is targetting the right MOB to mez. Would it be possible to make F8 (or some other way) cycle through all close-by Mobs if I press F8 more than once? Similar to F1-F1 to target your pet. F2-F2 should target the first party member's pet, but that's another request. Comments?<P>

<B>It's highly unlikely that we could implement this in a reasonable amount of time. It would require indexing of all creatures that are close enough, or on the current view screen, loading them into an array, and cycling the position of the array each time the button is pressed. The difficulty is that the array would have to be updated on each press to account for creatures that had entered or exited the range, making keeping a logical position in the array difficult. We could try going alphabetically based upon the true name of the NPC (a_moss_snake24) but it would still require loading NPCs into the "in range" list upon each press. <P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/011488.html">Abashi, how come Shadowknights never get Summon Corpse?</a></B><P>

Abashi, how come Shadowknights never get Summon Corpse? <P>

<B>Simply, because we decided that it would be a necro only spell. The fact that paladins get a version of resurrection is another matter entirely. <P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/011652.html">Abashi, where you guys went wrong on Monks.</a></B><P>

Cmon and reply Abashi.<P>

<B>Andy's post already covered it. Gloves can't have combat stats. Items with combat stats can't use the hand-to-hand skill. Yes, in retrospect it would have been nice to build this in from the begining, but it's not something that we can go back and change.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/011735.html">Uh oh..</a></B><P>

What *I* want is for Verant to do the decent thing and tell *her* why her player account was banned.<P>

<B>And we will, but that is not subject for discussion on the boards here. How we interact with the guide program is between us and the members of that program.</B><P>

I would think that the player account being banned should be answered given that no "PLAYER" rules of conduct were broken...<P>

<B>People who become guides become subject to the guide rules of conduct in addition to those for the average player. Yes, this means that someone can lose their player account by virtue of something done as a guide.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/011743.html">There sure are a lot of upset customers...</a></B><P>

I've been lurking here a while now and I have to admit that recently there seems to be a huge increase in the average level of player frustration with the game and Verant in general.<P>

<B>The number of daily posts total has been pretty much constant for 9 months now. My impression is that there's been a greater number of positive posts here on the board as of late.</B><P> 

So I am asking you, what do you think of all this? I can't imagine this recent rise in complaints has gone unnoticed. Is there any particular reason why so many decisions have been made lately which run contrary to popular opinion?<P> 

<B>Just because so many decisions are being made. Any decision has the potential of being in accord with or contrary to public opinion. The Live team has been hard at work making a lot of changes to the game, so it's natural that a greater number of decisions would be contrary, just as a greater number of decisions are in accord with public opinion.<P>

Please keep in mind how these boards work. People tend to voice dissatisfaction where they feel they will be heard. They are heard on this board. If you go look at Stratics or EQ Vaults forums, you'll see a far greater percentage of positive posts.<P>

Also, people are far more likely to get worked up by something that annoys them than something they are pleased with. It's pure human nature. That doesn't make the complaints any more or less valid, but it does speak to the percentage of posts on the board.<P> 

I'd say about 75% of the threads started, perhaps more, are to voice dissatisfaction with some element of gameplay. That does not mean that 75% of players are unhappy with the game as a whole, nor does it mean that 75% of people have the same issues. It just means that of the people motovated to post in our forum where they have a good chance of being heard, 75% choose to use the forum to get a particular issue of theirs addressed.</B><P>

Customer satisfaction has been steadily falling off for quite a few months now. <P>

<B>I disagree. Evidence points to it going up quite well. How I measure customer satisfaction is by those who go out of their way to praise the game, the team, and the changes that are made. Emails and positive posts here on the boards are up dramatically. <P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/011772.html">New or Old bug? I can proc any weapon at level 1 , can you? ( read abashi )</a></B><P>

I found a bug that allows ANYONE at ANY level to proc ANY weapon.<P>

<B>Sure, I'd appreciate it if you'd kick it over to me at <a href="mailto:gwrinn@verant.com">gwrinn@verant.com</a><P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/011774.html">ABASHI READ THIS</a></B><P>

The patch dosent work it always gives me the corrupt or missing file message. I called tech support and the only way i can play is if they send me the file. I did that and when I got a file I had trouble with the next file in the patch. It's testeverquest.ex_ I haven't been able to play for like 8 days; PLEASE HELP.<P>

<B>About the only explanation I can think of for what you are describing is that you probably have a virus on your system. I'd run some virus-check software. Failing that, you should probably give tech support a ring again.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/011787.html">Abashi just spill the beans already!</a></B><P>

Where is your big announcement of why you can't fix a simple and easily verifable bug (Bard Lullaby). Just face the music and do it already so we can get on with our lives.<P>

<B>It's posted at <a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum3/HTML/001610.html">this link</a>.<P>

-Gordon</B>
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
