				<font face="Verdana" size="1"><b>best</b></font>
			</td>
		</td>
		
	
	</tr>
	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				By Brell's frothy beard! Ye have really done it this time! Hail and well met, my name is Meinhard Stonecutter, Holy Warrior of Brell in my 33rd season of service and Master Smith. I have never spoken me voice about some of the things that ye have decided to post here, but I can't bite my tongue anymore! <BR>
<BR>
As I have mentioned, I be a Master Smith, having invested long hours of blazing-hot blood and tears at the forges in Kaladim and Freeport (Best steel west of Kaladim my arse!) It is my pride and joy to make banded armor and forged weapons for my guildmates, Clan of the Underfoot (on Quellious). I have long dreamed of the day when I could, of course, advance my skill to smith weapons and armor of such fine composition that it would move other dwarves to tears and earn me name a spot amongst the stars. . . sigh. Yet, now I fear that my dreams are dashed because of what I take as a personal insult, and hope is only a minor oversight. (Brace yerselves)<BR>
<BR>
As even the squireliest halfling and dumbest ogre can tell you: MITHRIL is a Dwarven metal, mined deep within the darkest recesses of Norrath, or any world for that matter! How in Brell's holy name (crosses self) did ye decide to let those.... (coughs) elves have it!? I have to go no further than the greatest Fantasy God of them all to site my correctness: J.R.R. Tolkien! <BR>
<BR>
It is from him that all fantasy rpgs spawned and took their lead. It is written clearly in the pages of the Silmarillion, the Hobbit and the War of the Ring: Mithril was discovered and first smithed by DWARVES!!!! Don't believe me, then read it fer yerself!<BR>
<BR>
Even more evidence comes from the Forgotten Realms series of books that feature every Ranger's wet dream: Drizzt Do'Urden (may have messed his name up, so forgive me ye stinking dark elves, ok?). Who can forget Bruenor's dream to find his home, &quot;Where the mithril ran like gleaming silver rivers deep into the mountains.&quot; <BR>
<BR>
What can be more convincing?<BR>
<BR>
Now don't get me wrong, I have lots of respect for those tree-hugging, faerie-loving, grass-eating, pointy-eared elves! No race can match their mastery of the woods (which we cut to fuel the fires of our mighty forges) or their ability in woodcrafting. They produce the finest in arrows and bows, not to mention that they are renowned for their jewel crafting and smithing abilities as well (not as well as dwarves of course).<BR>
<BR>
In fact, it was a High Elf that forged the most beautiful jewels ever made: the silmarils. His name was Feanor and he was named the greatest smith of all time for his forging of those jewels, a mere oversight since my ancestors were unknown at that point in time, but another matter.<BR>
<BR>
So now let's dispense with all these warm fuzzies! Ye have taken my birthright and I demand it back! It has yet to go live on the servers, so it is as simple as changing a name from Brellium to Mithril, and from Mithril to some other metal alloy you can think of. (If ye need help, I am a writer in real life and get paid to think of such things on a regular basis.) It is my dream to smith Mithril and you have robbed it from me! Just change the name and make millions of angry, hot-tempered, ale-guzzling, armor-making, knee-chopping dwarves happy!<BR>
<BR>
I hope ye'll post this so I can at least have a shot at convincing any like-minded folks in hopes of making a positive change. Besides, where the heck on Norrath do you find High Elves mining in earnest, where the Mithril is to be found? Name me a zone that could have this qualification? Come on! Kaladim is IN a mountain range, for Brell's sake! Felwithe is hidden within the comfort and safety of the mountains, deep in the protective arms of the mountain range inhabited by dwarves. Really, do you think a high elf would bother getting down and dirty into the belly of the core of the planet!? They might break a nail or something! And Brell forbid that happen!<BR>
<BR>
Mithril belongs with Dwarves! We earned as much, at least from getting shafted by other deals, i.e. Tree Weaves and such... like ANY race could wear what a giant wears... yeah! I mean you don't even have the basic blacksmithing tools in Kaladim! You have to go to Freeport (Brell love those silly humans) just to get your skill started! What sense does that make anyway? WE ARE DWARVES!!! What did you miss about that? WE make the BEST blacksmiths, traditionally, and deserve to have the honor of making Mithril. Give Brellium to the elves, if they can carry it. They might break a sweat and mess up their hair or something.  
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
